definition.value: a syndrome AE that has  dysfunction of the corticospinal (pyramidal) tracts of the spinal cord. Symptoms include an increase in the muscle tone in the lower extremities, hyperreflexia, positive Babinski and a decrease in fine motor coordination.
a brain edema AE that has  swelling due to an excessive accumulation of fluid in the brain.
a tumor AE that has  development of a malignancy most probably as a result of treatment for a previously existing malignancy.
a hemorrhage AE that has  bleeding from the cranium.

a death AE that has  death in utero; failure of the product of conception to show evidence of respiration, heartbeat, or definite movement of a voluntary muscle after expulsion from the uterus, without possibility of resuscitation.
a ischemia AEE that has a brief attack (less than 24 hours) of cerebral dysfunction of vascular origin, with no persistent neurological deficit.
afemale reproductive system AE that has  vaginal secretions. Mucus produced by the cervical glands is discharged from the vagina naturally, especially during the childbearing years.

a sensory capability AE that has  a sudden drop of the blood pressure, bradycardia, and peripheral vasodilation that may lead to loss of consciousness. It results from an increase in the stimulation of the vagus nerve.
apregnancy AE that has  delivery of a viable infant before the normal end of gestation. Typically, viability is achievable between the twentieth and thirty-seventh week of gestation.
a psychiatric disorder AE that has  excitement of psychotic proportions manifested by mental and physical hyperactivity, disorganization of behavior and elevation of mood.

a hair growth abnormal AE that has  the presence of excess hair growth in women in anatomic sites where growth is considered to be a secondary male characteristic and under androgen control (beard, moustache, chest, abdomen)
a necrosis AE that has a necrotic process occurring in the bone of the mandible.
a necrosis AE that has  a necrotic process occurring in the soft tissues of the abdominal wall.

a metabolic disorder AE that has  an increase in sensitivity to the adverse effects of alcohol, which can include nasal congestion, skin flushes, heart dysrhythmias, nausea, vomiting, indigestion and headaches.
a psychiatric disorder AE that has an inability to achieve orgasm.
an urinary system AE that has  a rupture in the bladder wall.
an urinary system AE that has  a sudden and involuntary contraction of the bladder wall.
a hemorrhage AE that is  bleeding from the bronchial wall and/or lung parenchyma.
a respiratory system AE that has blockage of a bronchus passage, most often by bronchial secretions and exudates.
a respiratory system AE that has a narrowing of the bronchial tube.
a necrosis AE that has a necrotic process occurring in the brain and/or spinal cord.
a pain AE that has marked discomfort sensation in the chest wall region.
a cystitis AE that has inflammation of the bladder which is not caused by an infection of the urinary tract.
a psychiatric disorder AE that has sexual dysfunction characterized by a delay in climax.
a male reproductive system AE that has  problems related to ejaculation. This category includes premature, delayed, retrograde and painful ejaculation.
a muscular weakness AE that has  a reduction in the strength of the facial muscles.
a female reproductive system AE that has blockage of the normal flow of the contents in the fallopian tube.
a female reproductive system AE that has a narrowing of the fallopian tube lumen.
a connective tissue disorder AE that has  shrinking of adipose tissue.
a fistula AE that has  an abnormal communication between a female reproductive system organ and another organ or anatomic site.
an endocrine system AE that has  the development of secondary female sex characteristics in males due to extrinsic factors.
a connective tissue disorder AE that has  fibrotic degeneration of the deep connective tissues.
a muscular weakness AE that has   a reduction in the strength of muscles in multiple anatomic sites.
a musculoskeletal and connective tissue AE that  has  stature that is smaller than normal as expected for age.
a necrosis AE that has  a necrotic process occurring in the soft tissues of the head.
a female reproductive system AE that has  the presence of blood in a fallopian tube.
a sleep disorder AE that has characterized by excessive sleepiness during the daytime.
a homeostasis AE that has accumulation of iron in the tissues.
an ischemia AE that has  a decrease or absence of blood supply to the brain caused by obstruction (thrombosis or embolism) of an artery resulting in neurological damage.
a cranial neuropathy AE that has  involvement of the trochlear nerve (fourth cranial nerve).

definition.value: a joint disorder AE that has a decrease in flexibility of a cervical spine joint.

label.value: joint range of motion decreased lumbar spine AE

definition.value: a joint disorder AE that has  a decrease in flexibility of a lumbar spine joint.
a fistula AE that has an abnormal communication between the larynx and another organ or anatomic site.
a hemorrhage AE that has bleeding from the larynx.
an inflammation AE that has an inflammation involving the mucous membrane of the larynx.
a respiratory system AE that has blockage of the laryngeal airway.
a libido disorder AE that has a decrease in sexual desire.
a libido disorder AE that has  an increase in sexual desire.
a skin AE that has hypertrophy of the subcutaneous adipose tissue at the site of multiple subcutaneous injections of insulin.
an immune system AE that has  the loss of lymph fluid into the surrounding tissue or body cavity.
